{{coord|49|01|18|N|111|37|29|E|display=title|region:MN}}

[[File:Delun-Boldog 2.JPG|thumb|[[Ovoo]] and monument at the site]]
'''Dulüün-Boldog''', or '''Delun-Boldog''' is a site located in [[Dadal]], [[Khentii Province|Khentii]] that is considered to be the birthplace of [[Genghis Khan]]. It is frequently referenced in Mongol folklore, has a sacrosanct reputation among Mongols, and is located in a rural area made up entirely of small towns and villages. A large statue of the Khan was built 1962 for his 800th birthday in 1162.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.discovermongolia.mn/country_travel_destinations_eastern_Mongolia.htm#&panel1-3|publisher = www.discovermongolia.mn |title=Eastern Mongolia |accessdate=20 March 2012}}</ref>

