{{Infobox building |name = Gaillard Center |image = |image size = |caption = |building_type = Mixed Use |location = [[Charleston, South Carolina]] |alternate_names = |coordinates = |status = Completed |roof = |antenna_spire = |floor_count = |est_completion = |floor_area = |architect = David Schwartz |main_contractor = |concrete_contractor = |management = }} The '''Gaillard Center''' is a concert hall and performance venue in [[Charleston, South Carolina]]. It was opened in 2015 and replaced the Gaillard Municipal Auditorium. Constructing the new facility was a central priority of mayor [[Joseph P. Riley Jr.|Joe Riley’s]] administration. The opening, planned for early 2015 in time for the city's [[Spoleto Festival USA|Spoleto Festival]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.postandcourier.com/features/arts_and_travel/gaillard-center-announces-programming-for-inaugural-season/article_942eec59-b583-565e-8e02-a89c55df7782.html|title=Gaillard Center announces programming for inaugural season|last=Parker|first=Adam|date=5 June 2015|publisher=Charleston Post and Courier|accessdate=5 April 2018}}</ref> was delayed by six months due to overages.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://abcnews4.com/archive/gaillard-center-opening-delayed-for-perfection|title=$142 million Gaillard Center opening delayed for 'perfection'|date=12 November 2014|publisher=ABC4|accessdate=5 April 2018}}</ref> [[Yo-Yo Ma]] performed at the opening of the center.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.postandcourier.com/features/arts_and_travel/grand-gaillard-blessed-by-yo-yo-ma-concert-hall-shines/article_a21371cd-4be0-5b29-8fbb-5f10545a4aec.html|title=Grand Gaillard Blessed by Yo-Yo Ma, concert hall shines in opening gala|last=Parker|first=Adam|date=17 October 2015|publisher=Charleston Post and Courier|accessdate=5 April 2018}}</ref>
