{{Unreferenced|date=April 2007}}[[File:Mancos Shale badlands in Capitol Reef NP.jpg|thumb|Gray slope-forming [[Mancos Shale]] below resistant sandstone caprock in the Capital Reef area of Utah]]
A '''slope-former''' is a unit of [[bedrock]] which is less resistant to [[erosion]] than overlying or underlying units and consequently results in [[outcrop]]s with low relative slope angles.  It may be contrasted with [[cliff-former]].  Typical slope forming lithologies include [[shale]]s, and [[limestone]]s in humid environments.

{{DEFAULTSORT:Slope-Former}}
